description: A textual string containing the alert's category (probable cause)
variables.name: TURIN-MIB::eatPrbCause

description: 1 = Critical
2 = Major
3 = Minor
4 = Warning
5 = Clear
6 = Info
Values of 1 to 4 indicates that an an alarm is raised
5 indicates that an alarm is cleared
and 6 indicates that it is only an event.
variables.name: TURIN-MIB::eatSeverity

description: A textual string containing the alert's description.
variables.name: TURIN-MIB::eatMsg

description: The alert creation time, in number of seconds since 1/1/1970 (GMT Time)
variables.name: TURIN-MIB::eatTime

description: The IP address of the host where the source of the alert resides
variables.name: TURIN-MIB::eatSourceIpAddress

description: A textual string containing the type of the source of the alert
variables.name: TURIN-MIB::eatSourceType
